we use grunt script to build the application to his minify version
and send it to the server using sftp protocol.

REQUIREMENTS:
you need to download and install nodeJS at the following link : 
http://nodejs.org/download/

this nodeJs applications contains all the npm (node package manager) required by Grunt to download required modules
for more information: http://gruntjs.com/

INSTRUCTIONS:
1) open command line in the root folder
2) install globally grunt-cli with the command line : "npm install -g grunt-cli" (first time only)
3) update the dependencies modules with the command line "npm install" (every time the package.json is modified)
   (will loop on packages.json file config and download required modules to build the project)
4) build the project with the command line "grunt"
